As noetic is archived, you may face errors with some dependencies, you may need to build them manually.

Also note each time build fails, clear the previous incomplete build and start again
rm -rf build devel

1. For building cv_bridge manually 
You need to be in the catkin_ws/src folder

git clone https://github.com/ros-perception/vision_opencv.git
cd vision_opencv/
git checkout noetic
cd ..

2. For building image_transport manually

git clone https://github.com/ros-perception/image_common.git
cd image_common/
git checkout noetic-devel
cd ..

3. If you get boost errors (cannot find a specific version) in /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/
ln -s /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/libboost_python3.so libboost_python37.so #assumes you have libboost_python3.so but your code is looking for libboost_python37.so

4. yaml-cpp errors
git clone https://github.com/jbeder/yaml-cpp.git
cd yaml-cpp/
git checkout yaml-cpp-0.6.3
mkdir build
cd build
cmake .. -DCMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE=ON
make -j4
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig
export CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/usr/local:$CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH
cd ../..
